During the era of the Warring States, these lands were part of the Qi kingdom. When the Qin kingdom united China into a single state for the first time in history, Boyang County (博阳县) was created here. Under the Han Empire, it was renamed Boxian (博县) and subordinated to the county Taishan (泰山郡); authorities of the Taishan district until 110 BC. e. they were located precisely in the administrative center of Boxian County. Under the Northern Wei Empire, Boxian County was renamed Boping (博平县) and the authorities of Taishan County were again transferred to it. Under the Northern Qi Empire, the county was again renamed Boxian; At the same time, Taishan County was disbanded, and the county was subordinated to Dongping County (东平郡).